 <title>Thermal Expansion</title>
 
 <introduction>
 <p>
  You may have observed that Jammed lid of a bottle can be easily unscrewed 
  if it is put into the hot water for sometime. A partially inflated balloon 
  expands to full size when placed in lukewarm water. A fully inflated balloon begins 
  shrinking when immersed in cold water. Most materials expand on heating and contract 
  on cooling. The physical property of a material due to which a body can change its 
  dimensions with a change in temperature is called a <term>thermal expansion</term>. 
  The expansion in length is called <em>linear expansion</em>, the expansion in area is called 
  <em>superficial expansion</em>, and the expansion in volume is called <em>volumetric expansion.</em> or bulk expansion.
 </p>
